    <div class="text">
    	<h2>Ingredients</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>1 tbsp Olive Oil </li>
            <li>1 Onion</li>
            <li>2 cloves Garlic</li>
            <li>2-3 Peppers (different colours)</li>
            <li> 250g Mushrooms (approx 1 packet) </li>
            <li>1 Fajita Seasoning (either use a packet or add 3/4 tsp cumin, 1 tsp paprika, 3/4 tsp salt, 3/4 tsp chili powder)</li>
            <li>6-8 Tortilla wraps</li>
            <li>Optional extras: Refried beans, Salsa, Avocado, Vegan Cheese</li>
                                       
        </ul>
        
</div>

</div>
<div class="method">
    	<h2>Method</h2>

        <p>Slice the onion, peppers and mushrooms thickly and mince the garlic</p>
        <p>Heat the oil in a large skillet</p>
        <p>Add the onion and cook for 2-3 minutes.</p>
        <p>Add in the peppers, mushrooms, garlic and seasoning. Cook until vegetables just begin to soften (about 10 minutes).</p>
        <p>Place tortilla wraps on a plate and heat in the microwave for 30 seconds. Alternatively wrap in foil and heat in the oven for 10 minutes at 180C.</p>
        <p>Bring the skille to the table on a heat proof mat and build your own fajitas how you like them.</p>
        
        
    </br></br>

</div>
        
